        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 30 at 9:55PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 955 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles west of Groom, or 11 miles northeast of Claude, moving south at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Groom.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
